  stimulus_text = 'The author’s argument is that the "real thing"—in this case, a natural environment—is more compelling and realistic than a computer-generated image. This argument is supported by the author’s use of the word "prohibitively." This word suggests that using practical effects is often too expensive, which may lead filmmakers to use a blended approach. What is the most likely reason why the author uses the word "prohibitively"?',
