  correct_answer = 'A',
  explanation = 'The main point of the passage is that learning by doing is the best way to learn about new ideas. The author supports this point by explaining that learning by doing allows people to experience the idea firsthand, which can help them to understand it more deeply. The author then provides an example to illustrate this point: a student who learns about the human body by reading a textbook may not understand the complex interactions of the different systems as well as a student who dissects a frog. This example highlights the key point of the passage: learning by doing is the best way to learn about new ideas. The passage states that "Many people believe that the best way to understand a new idea is to read about it in a book or article. However, scient…", which is the textual anchor for eliminating weaker choices. Choice A is correct because it aligns with that evidence: learning by doing is the best way to learn about new ideas.. Each incorrect option either contradicts a explicit detail, imports information not present in the text, or answers a different question than the one asked.',
